begin_memory_text: At the beginning of the conversation, Matt and I introduced ourselves and talked about the weather in our respective states.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation, Matt and I were discussing the handling of the pandemic, potential long-term effects of the way it is being handled, and other personal details.
end_memory_text: At the end of the conversation, Matt and I exchanged general pleasantries and talked about how frustrating it is to attempt to hold productive conversations with Trump supporters.
rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week being amazing. I do not know exactly what is going to happen, but each day has the potential to be better than the rest. I am currently in a new relationship and she makes every day seem like a treasure. I am also recently motivated to be more productive in regards to my classwork and hobbies.
critical_positive: Matt is very good at giving off a non-judgemental aura, so whenever I spoke I didn't feel as though he wanted me to stop nor did I ever feel like he was annoyed. We were both pretty good listeners, allowing the other to speak until they stopped and resuming when there was a comfortable pause or silence. We also have similar views on things that are central to our current situations, which guided most of the conversation.
critical_negative: The only times I felt like the conversation was a bit stilted was when I interrupted Matt. I did this 2 times, I think. I was too excited to respond to what he had just said. There was also a moment where I think I spoke for a bit too long but Matt didn't really seem to mind.

begin_memory_text: In the beginning we started asking questions of where we were, name, what was going on, how people were handling the pandemic and being on lock down.
middle_memory_text: we were sharing how we both disliked not having the same policies from town to town, state to state, or anything federal pushed down to all state so even if someone where to visit someone else, who knows if they were being safe this entire time or now possibly infecting people from being careless.
end_memory_text: towards the end we had civil political debate though we were on the same side we helped share the misery each of us felt but showed how we were working through it and when our return to normalcy was (if ever) was going to be like instead of where we are at currently.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of the week will be the same im sure but hearing from someone in another state having the same issues is new and refreshing just to hear that others are having the same feelings and uncertainties. To bond with someone else about the same misery we've all been living with and dealing with was a nice therapeutic break.
critical_positive: Because the person was friendly it was easy to start chatting and once you got a feeling of their level of empathy and were potentially on the same brain wave lengths it was easier to open up and discuss and have a nice going back and forth conversation even about the crap pandemic we're currently in.
critical_negative: There was not really any issues - it went without any hitches. There was no real lag in conversation or from technology. The talk kept flowing pretty well and we obviously made it to a little over 50 minutes in general chatting without even trying. So that was a pleasant surprise. I was worried about myself keeping going and hitting that time limit but it went by very fast and even over time.
